<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="M" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Marble" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Marble,</orth> the stone Marmor; used for monuments <bibl n="shak. son 55.1" default="NO" valid="yes">Sonn. 55, 1</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h8 3.2.434" default="NO" valid="yes">H8 III, 2, 434</bibl>. Adjectively: Meas. V <bibl n="shak. h8 3.2.434" default="NO" valid="yes">H8 III, 2, 434</bibl> <bibl n="shak. ham 1.4.50" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. I, 4, 50</bibl>. Emblem of hardness: <bibl n="shak. luc 560" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 560</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. luc 560" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 560</bibl> <bibl n="shak. mm 3.1.238" default="NO" valid="yes">Meas. III, 1, 238</bibl> <cit><quote>(a m. to her tears).</quote> <bibl n="shak. err 2.1.93" default="NO" valid="yes">Err. II, 1, 93</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. 3h6 3.2.50" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C III, 2, 50</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tit 2.3.144" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. II, 3, 144</bibl>. Adjectively: <bibl n="shak. luc 1240" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 1240</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wt 5.2.98" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. V, 2, 98</bibl> <cit><quote>(who was most m. there changed colour).</quote> <bibl n="shak. 3h6 3.1.38" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C III, 1, 38</bibl></cit>. Used of the heavens (on account of their eternity?) <bibl n="shak. oth 3.3.460" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. III, 3, 460</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cym 5.4.87" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. V, 4, 87</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cym 5.4.87" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. V, 4, 87</bibl> cf. <cit><quote>Marbled. whole as the m.</quote> <bibl n="shak. mac 3.4.22" default="NO" valid="yes">Mcb. III, 4, 22</bibl></cit>; cf. <bibl n="shak. wt 2.3.90" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. II, 3, 90</bibl>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>